      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <versionCode>00</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2019-07-05</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2019-12-31T19:29:36Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Appraisal Reform Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill revises provisions related to real estate appraisals. Specifically, the bill </p> <ul> <li>adds trainee appraisers to the National Registry of Appraisers, </li> <li>allows the Federal Financial Institutions Examination Council's Appraisal Subcommittee to adjust annual registry fees for appraisal management companies, </li> <li>requires the disclosure of appraisal fees in the case of an appraisal coordinated by an appraisal management company, </li> <li>allows nonprofit organizations and institutions of higher education to receive certain grants, and </li> <li>adds a designee of the Department of Veterans Affairs to the Appraisal Subcommittee. </li> </ul>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-07-05T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
        </item>
        <item>
          <versionCode>53</versionCode>
          <actionDate>2019-09-19</actionDate>
          <actionDesc>Passed House</actionDesc>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2020-01-02T15:05:54Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Appraisal Fee Transparency Act of 2019</b></p> <p>This bill revises provisions related to real estate appraisals. Specifically, the bill </p> <ul> <li>adds trainee appraisers to the National Registry of Appraisers, </li> <li>allows the Federal Financial Institutions Examination Council's Appraisal Subcommittee to adjust annual registry fees for appraisal management companies, </li> <li>requires the disclosure of appraisal fees in the case of an appraisal coordinated by an appraisal management company, </li> <li>allows nonprofit organizations and institutions of higher education to receive certain grants, and </li> <li>adds a designee of the Department of Veterans Affairs to the Appraisal Subcommittee. </li> </ul>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2019-09-19T12:35:45Z</updateDate>
          <name>Passed House</name>
        </item>
